HEADWORD: Melluco
<hw>Mel*lu"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A climbing plant (<spn>Ullucus officinalis</spn>) of the Andes,
having tuberous roots which are used as a substitute for
potatoes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melne</ent>⟦br⟧
